text:
Fulton Street, south side, east from the East River, showing the Fulton Street Elevated Line and station. At the right are the E.R. Squibb and Son buildings, which are located on the S.E. and S.W. corners of Columbia Heights and Doughty Street.
April 4, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

Columbia Heights, no.65-71, Brooklyn.
Federal Art Project, "Changing New York," photographs by Berenice Abbott.  Title: "Brooklyn Facade"
May 14, 1936
title: Brooklyn: Columbia Heights.
